# Git Workflow
**AI Web Dev Agency — Internal Reference**
Last updated: July 2026

---

## Repo Structure

**One repo per client project.**

Each client gets its own GitHub repository. No monorepo. Reasons:
- Clean handover: give a client their repo without exposing other projects
- Independent history: one project's bad commit doesn't affect another
- GitHub Pages works per-repo (useful for client preview links)
- Access control stays simple

### Naming Convention

```
agency-[clientname]-[projecttype]

Examples:
  agency-eurletb-website
  agency-clientname-landing
  agency-clientname-portfolio
```

---

## Initial Setup (Per Project)

```bash
# 1. Create the repo on GitHub (private by default)
#    Go to github.com → New repository → name it → Private → Create

# 2. Clone it locally
git clone https://github.com/YOUR_USERNAME/agency-clientname-website.git
cd agency-clientname-website

# 3. Add your project files
cp -r /path/to/project/* .

# 4. Create .gitignore
touch .gitignore

# 5. First commit
git add .
git commit -m "init: project scaffold and initial files"
git push origin main
```

### Recommended `.gitignore`
```
# OS
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db

# Editor
.vscode/
.cursor/
*.code-workspace

# Logs & temp
*.log
*.tmp

# Large assets (add manually with git-lfs or keep out of repo)
images/raw/
*.psd
*.ai
```

