## Branch Strategy

Simple two-branch model — no overhead, safe enough for solo work.

```
main      ← stable, client-deliverable state only
dev       ← active work, agent outputs, experiments
```

### Daily workflow:
```bash
# Always work on dev
git checkout dev

# When a full pipeline stage is done and verified, merge to main
git checkout main
git merge dev
git push origin main
```

---

## Commit at Every Pipeline Stage

This is the core habit. One commit per pipeline stage, every time.

| Stage | Tool | Commit Message Format | Example |
|---|---|---|---|
| 1 — Plan | Claude Sonnet 5 | `plan: [description]` | `plan: services page architecture and prompt set` |
| 2 — Generate | Gemini 3.5 Flash / DeepSeek V3.2 | `generate: [description]` | `generate: services page HTML/CSS from DeepSeek V3` |
| 3 — Integrate | Antigravity (Gemini 3 Pro) | `integrate: [description]` | `integrate: services sections merged into services.html` |
| 4 — QA | Antigravity (Gemini 3 Pro) | `qa: [description]` | `qa: responsiveness fixed at 768px and 375px` |
| 5 — Review | Claude Sonnet 5 | `review: [description]` | `review: UX pass, hero padding and CTA copy adjusted` |

### Why this matters:
If Stage 3 breaks the layout, you can instantly return to Stage 2:
```bash
git log --oneline        # find the Stage 2 commit hash
git checkout abc1234     # go back to that exact state
```

