## GitHub Pages — Client Preview Links

For static sites (HTML/CSS/JS, no server), GitHub Pages gives you a free public preview URL to share with clients during review.

```bash
# Enable in: GitHub repo → Settings → Pages → Source: main branch / root
# URL will be: https://YOUR_USERNAME.github.io/agency-clientname-website/
```

Use this at Stage 5 (Review) — share the link with the client instead of sending files.

---

## Handover to Client

When the project is complete:

1. Make sure `main` is clean and fully up to date
2. Tag the final release:
   ```bash
   git tag v1.0 -m "Final delivery — [client name] — [date]"
   git push origin v1.0
   ```
3. Transfer repo ownership (if client wants it) via GitHub → Settings → Transfer
4. Or: add client as collaborator with read-only access

